# Ship / Release Workflow

When the user asks to **build and ship**, **ship**, **release**, or **push to TestFlight / Play**:

## 1. Bump store numbers first (required)

Do **not** run `eas build` or publish an OTA until native build numbers are bumped when shipping a **new binary** or when the marketing/runtime version changes.

| Goal | Command |
|------|---------|
| Same marketing version (`expo.version`), new iOS build + Android `versionCode` only | `npm run release:bump:build-only` |
| New patch version + build numbers + `runtimeVersion` + `package.json` | `npm run release:bump` |

The script updates `app.json` (iOS `buildNumber`, Android `versionCode`, and optionally `version` / `runtimeVersion`) and runs `sync-native-version.js` so `android/app/build.gradle` matches.

- **OTA only** (`eas update`): If you are **not** producing a new store binary, you usually **do not** bump native build numbers; only bump **`runtimeVersion`** (via `release:bump`) when the JS bundle must target a new runtime.

## 2. Commit version bumps

Commit `app.json`, `package.json` (if changed), `android/app/build.gradle` (if present), then push.

## 3. Native builds (TestFlight / Play)

```bash
eas build --platform all --profile production --non-interactive
```

Optional: add `--auto-submit` if your Expo project is configured for automatic submission.

## 4. Submit to stores (if not using auto-submit)

```bash
eas submit --platform ios --latest --non-interactive
eas submit --platform android --latest --non-interactive
```

## 5. Manual Gradle sync (only if you skipped the bump script)

```bash
npm run release:sync-version
```
